  "description": [
    "12 PLANS REVISE IMMIGRATION LAW Representative Johnson See ing U S Being Undermined Favors Reduced Quotas BY FREDERIC WILLIAM WILE Alleging that the morals ideals lit erature journalism drama and en the physical stature of the American people are being steadily undermined bv foreign blood Representative Al bert Johnson Republican of Wash ington will ask the Seventieth Con gress for new and drastic curtailment of immigration The bill which he will push to that end would cut the present total of admissible aliensfrom roundly 160000 to approximately 75000 It would limit the maximum quota for any country after July 1 1928 to 25000 which would more than halve the existing largest quota that of Germany 51227 The quota of Great Britain and northern Ire land now 34007 would also be seri ously affected The Irish Free State s immigrant allowance would be whit tled down by more than 3000 per annum Would Reduce Quotas Mr Johnson the veteran chairman of the House immigration committee and principal author of the immigra tion law of 1924 now in force pro poses that all quotas shall be reduced 10 per cent a year after July 1 1925 and until July 1 1933 After"
